# Phonebook-Driven E2E Test Generation

Use the Hz Squirrel "phonebook" (user-spec) as the source of truth for generating comprehensive Playwright e2e tests in FFP. The phonebook
lives at `apps/squirrel/user-spec/` in the Hz repo ([PR #273242](https://git.corp.adobe.com/Horizon/hz/pull/273242)) and documents every
behavior rule, dimension variant, and acceptance criterion for Squirrel features — derived from PRDs and the current Hz implementation.

The phonebook stays in Hz. We read it remotely (via `gh api`) when generating tests — no local copy in FFP.

The phonebook also includes an **implementation map** (`apps/squirrel/user-spec/implementation-map.md`) that organizes 78 spec files into 20
epics with dependency ordering, AC counts per file (813 AC + 159 PERF-AC = 972 total), and a risk/complexity summary. We use the
implementation map to understand epic scope and dependencies, but the individual spec files are the source of truth for test generation.

## Why

Our current e2e tests cover happy paths but miss edge cases. For example, delete has 9 acceptance criteria in the phonebook; we test 3. The
phonebook's dimension analysis tables enumerate every meaningful variant (track type x connection state x selection mode x ...) — exactly
the combinatorial matrix we need to catch regressions, no matter how edge-case.

## Goals

1. **Regression safety net**: Any behavior change — however small — should fail at least one e2e test.
2. **Feature parity tracking**: Tests generated from the phonebook tell us where FFP matches Hz and where it diverges.
3. **TDD for upcoming features**: Unimplemented features get `test.fixme()` tests. When the feature ships, remove fixme, write the body,
   run. If it passes without changes, the implementation matches spec.

## Ground Rules

1. **Hz is the source of truth.** The phonebook describes how Squirrel should behave. If FFP doesn't match, it's either a bug or a
   not-yet-implemented feature. There is no "FFP-divergent" category. If we later discover a legitimate reason to differ, that's a
   conversation — not a default assumption.
2. **This will become a Claude Code skill: `/convert-feature-to-e2e`.** The user says which phonebook section to pick up, subagents do the
   work: read the phonebook spec, audit FFP support, generate the spec file, run it, update the status board.
3. **Old tests retire when new ones have complete coverage.** Existing hand-written tests (e.g. `delete.spec.ts`) stay until the
   phonebook-generated tests cover all the same ground. Then we remove the old ones to avoid duplication.

---

## High-Level Strategy

### 1. Triage each phonebook entry against FFP capabilities

Before generating tests from a phonebook file, classify every behavior and acceptance criterion:

| Classification      | Meaning                                          | Test treatment                                        |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| **Implemented**     | FFP supports this today                          | Generate test steps, expect them to **pass**          |
| **Not implemented** | Feature or prerequisite doesn't exist in FFP yet | Generate as `test.fixme()` — separate test, zero cost |
| **Not applicable**  | Hz-only feature with no FFP equivalent           | Don't generate                                        |

### 2. Generate tests per feature area

For each phonebook file, produce a **small number of tests** that chain related ACs and dimension variants together as `test.step()`
sequences. Each test loads the page once and exercises a logical flow of related behaviors, using undo/redo to reset state between steps
when needed.

Each test covers:

- Multiple related **acceptance criteria** as sequential steps within a single test
- **"Varies" dimension combinations** that represent meaningfully different code paths, grouped by the dimension axis (e.g. one test for
  "delete by track type", another for "delete edge cases")
- **Error states** woven into the flow where natural (e.g. "delete with nothing selected" before selecting and deleting)
- **Keyboard shortcut variants** tested alongside their mouse equivalents (e.g. Delete key then Backspace in the same test)

**Unimplemented features** get their own lightweight `test.fixme()` tests — separate from the implemented tests so they don't abort passing
steps. These fixme tests cost nothing (they bail before loading a page) but show up in the report as a TODO list. When the feature ships,
remove the `test.fixme()` line, write the test body to spec, and run. See "Fixme Pattern for Unimplemented Features" below.

### 3. Prioritize by risk

Don't boil the ocean. Order of attack:

| Priority | Feature area         | Phonebook file          | Why                                             |
| -------- | -------------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | **Delete**           | `delete.md`             | Simplest, clear ACs, good prototype             |
| 2        | **Split**            | `split.md`              | Similarly scoped, few dimensions                |
| 3        | **Trim**             | `trim.md`               | Complex (30+ scenarios), high regression risk   |
| 4        | **Selection**        | `selection.md`          | Foundation for everything else                  |
| 5        | **Move/reorder**     | `move.md`               | Within-track works; cross-track not implemented |
| 6        | **Gapless behavior** | `gapless-behavior.md`   | Cross-cutting rules, tested indirectly today    |
| 7        | **Snapping**         | `snapping.md`           | Core logic works; visual polish incomplete      |
| 8        | **Zoom/scroll/pan**  | `zoom-scroll-pan.md`    | Implemented, under-tested                       |
| 9        | **Playhead & ruler** | `playhead-and-ruler.md` | Implemented, under-tested                       |
| 10+      | **Everything else**  | Various                 | As features land in FFP                         |

---

## Per-Feature Workflow

When processing a single phonebook entry (e.g. `delete.md`):

### Step 1: Read the phonebook spec

Fetch remotely via `gh api`:

```bash
GH_HOST=git.corp.adobe.com gh api \
  'repos/Horizon/hz/contents/apps/squirrel/user-spec/04-timeline/delete.md?ref=natkin/phonebook' \
  | python3 -c "import sys,json,base64; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(base64.b64decode(d['content']).decode())"
```

Identify:

- **Behaviors** (each is a potential test or test group)
- **Acceptance criteria** (each AC maps to one or more test steps)
- **Dimension analysis "Varies" table** (each row is a parameter axis; combinations = test variants)
- **Error states** (negative tests)
- **Keyboard shortcuts** (verify each one)

### Step 2: Check FFP feature support

For each behavior / AC / dimension variant, answer:

> "Can I exercise this in FFP today?"

Checklist:

- [ ] Does the UI element exist? (e.g., freeform tracks exist, trim handles exist)
- [ ] Does the interaction work? (e.g., can I actually delete on a freeform track)
- [ ] Are prerequisite features present? (e.g., "connected deletion" requires connections — not in FFP)
- [ ] Does FFP use the same keyboard shortcuts?
- [ ] Is the test data setup capable of creating the precondition? (e.g., `createTestTracks()` creates freeform tracks, so AC-002 is
      testable)

Classify each: **implemented** (test steps, expect pass), **not implemented** (separate `test.fixme()`), or **not applicable** (skip, don't
generate).

### Step 3: Generate the test file

**Before writing a single line of test code, read these files in order:**

1. `docs/studio-e2e-guide.md` — 15 mandatory rules (source of truth). Non-negotiable.
2. `e2e/squirrel/tests/timeline-smoke.spec.ts` — gold standard structural template. Copy the shape.
3. `e2e/squirrel/pages/timeline-page.ts` — all available page object methods. Never invent an interaction that could use an existing method.
4. `e2e/squirrel/README.md` — all testids and locators.

Then generate. Then run `/e2e-review` on the output before declaring done.

**The most common mistakes that the guide forbids:**

- `expect.poll(() => locator.count())` when `expect(locator).toHaveCount(n)` exists
- `await locator.isVisible()` as a bare read instead of `await expect(locator).toBeVisible()`
- `page.waitForTimeout()` — banned, always
- Missing `expect(consoleErrors).toEqual([])` at the end of every test
- Missing `await timelinePage.focusTimeline()` before keyboard shortcuts
- Importing from `@playwright/test` instead of `../fixtures/squirrel.fixture.js`

**Principle: minimize page loads, maximize coverage per test.** Each `test()` loads the page once and chains related ACs as `test.step()`
calls. Use undo/redo to reset state between steps. Group steps by logical theme (e.g. "delete by track type", "delete edge cases & error
states").

Structure:

```typescript
test.describe('Delete — Phonebook', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ studioPage }) => {
    await studioPage.open();
  });

  test('delete by track type', async ({ timelinePage }) => {
    await timelinePage.waitForReady();

    await test.step('AC-001: delete on gapless closes gap', async () => {
      // select B on gapless, press Delete
      // assert C shifted left adjacent to A
    });

    await timelinePage.undo();

    await test.step('AC-002: delete on freeform leaves gap', async () => {
      // select clip on freeform, press Delete
      // assert neighbors didn't move
    });

    await timelinePage.undo();

    await test.step('AC-003: multi-delete across track types', async () => {
      // select clips on gapless + freeform, press Delete
      // assert gapless rippled, freeform left gaps
    });

    await timelinePage.undo();

    await test.step('Backspace triggers same behavior as Delete', async () => {
      // repeat a delete using Backspace, verify same result
    });
  });

  test('delete edge cases and error states', async ({ timelinePage }) => {
    await timelinePage.waitForReady();

    await test.step('AC-007: selection cleared after delete', async () => {
      // delete a clip, assert no selection
    });

    await timelinePage.undo();

    await test.step('AC-005: delete is undoable', async () => {
      // delete, undo, assert clip restored
    });

    await test.step('error: delete with nothing selected is no-op', async () => {
      // deselect all, press Delete, assert nothing changed
    });
  });

  // --- Unimplemented features: separate fixme tests ---
  // These bail immediately (no page load), but show in reports as TODOs.
  // When the feature ships, remove test.fixme(), write the body, run.

  test('AC-008: connected deletion cascades', async ({ timelinePage }) => {
    test.fixme(true, 'connections not in FFP — phonebook delete.md AC-008');
    // select gapless clip with connected freeform item
    // press Delete
    // assert both gapless and connected freeform items removed
    // assert remaining clips ripple correctly
  });

  test('AC-009: post-delete collision bumping', async ({ timelinePage }) => {
    test.fixme(true, 'connections not in FFP — phonebook delete.md AC-009');
    // delete gapless clip causing connected freeform items to collide
    // assert colliding item bumped to another track
  });

  test('delete clip with transition removes transition', async ({ timelinePage }) => {
    test.fixme(true, 'transitions not in FFP — phonebook delete.md');
    // add transition between A and B
    // delete A
    // assert transition is also removed
  });
});
```

#### Fixme Pattern for Unimplemented Features

`test.fixme()` inside a test **aborts the entire test** (not just the step). So unimplemented features always go in **separate tests**,
never as steps inside passing tests. This way:

- Implemented tests run fully and show as "passed"
- Fixme tests show as "skipped" in reports — a built-in TODO list
- Fixme tests cost nothing (they bail before loading a page)
- When the feature ships, remove `test.fixme()`, write the body, run — if it passes, the implementation matches the phonebook

Why `test.fixme` instead of `test.skip`:

- Both abort the test, but they show up as different categories in the report
- `fixme` signals "this should work eventually" — it's a TODO
- `skip` signals "intentionally not running" — it's a decision (bugs, platform limitations)
- The report becomes a feature-readiness dashboard: when fixme count drops, you're closer to parity

Naming convention: `{feature}-phonebook.spec.ts` (e.g. `delete-phonebook.spec.ts`).

#### Test infrastructure reference

Tests use the existing FFP Squirrel e2e fixtures and page objects:

| File                                        | What it provides                                                                     |
| ------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| `e2e/squirrel/fixtures/squirrel.fixture.ts` | `test`, `expect` imports, `studioPage`, `timelinePage`, `consoleErrors` fixtures     |
| `e2e/squirrel/pages/timeline-page.ts`       | `TimelinePage` — all timeline interactions (select, delete, trim, split, undo, etc.) |
| `e2e/squirrel/pages/studio-page.ts`         | `StudioPage` — page load, navigation, config                                         |

Read these before generating tests to understand available helper methods (e.g., `timelinePage.startTrimDrag()`,
`timelinePage.deleteSelected()`, `timelinePage.gaplessTrackItems`, `timelinePage.freeformTrackItems`). If a phonebook AC requires an
interaction not yet in the page object, add the method to the page object as part of the generation step.

### Step 4: Run and classify results

After generating, run the tests. Every test is written to the Hz phonebook spec — Hz is the source of truth.

- **All steps pass** — FFP matches the phonebook for those ACs. Done.
- **A step fails because the behavior is wrong** — this is a bug in FFP. The test is correct. Add
  `test.skip(true, 'BUG: [description] — filed as [ticket]')` and file the bug. The test stays as-is; when the bug is fixed, remove the
  skip.
- **A step fails because a prerequisite feature doesn't exist** — this should have been caught in Step 2. Convert to a separate
  `test.fixme()` test.
- **fixme tests** — show in report as pending. When the feature ships, remove fixme, write the body, run.

### Step 5: Update status board

After a feature's phonebook tests are generated and run, update the Status Board below with AC counts and results. Also update the coverage
table comment at the top of the spec file.

---

## FFP Feature Audit (as of 2026-04-10)

Ground truth from source code audit — what's actually implemented, not what tests exist for.

### Fully Implemented

These features work end-to-end in FFP and are **ready for phonebook e2e generation**:

| Feature                      | Key capabilities                                                                                                           | Phonebook file          | Phonebook gaps (fixme candidates)                              |
| ---------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Delete**                   | Delete/Backspace, gapless ripple, freeform gap-left, multi-delete, empty track auto-removal, selection cleared, undoable   | `delete.md`             | Connections (AC-008, AC-009), transitions                      |
| **Split**                    | S key (at playhead), Shift+S (split tool mode), multi-select split, preserves clip properties, Escape exits tool           | `split.md`              | Connections, transitions                                       |
| **Trim**                     | 8px drag handles, gapless ripple trim, freeform slip trim, Q/W keyboard trim, multi-select Q/W, duration tooltip, clamping | `trim.md`               | Connections (delayed bumping), transitions (0.2s removal rule) |
| **Selection**                | Click, Cmd/Ctrl+click (toggle), marquee/lasso, Cmd+A, mixed kind/mode selection, contiguous constraint on gapless drag     | `selection.md`          | —                                                              |
| **Playback**                 | Space play/pause, arrow keys (1 frame), Shift+arrow (10 frames), Cmd+Up/Down (start/end), auto-scroll                      | `playback.md`           | —                                                              |
| **Undo/Redo**                | Cmd+Z / Cmd+Shift+Z, all operations produce undo steps, continuous drags coalesced                                         | `undo-redo.md`          | —                                                              |
| **Zoom/Scroll/Pan**          | `=`/`-`/`\` keys, Ctrl+scroll, zoom centered on cursor                                                                     | `zoom-scroll-pan.md`    | Autoscroll hot-zone behavior                                   |
| **Playhead & Ruler**         | Click ruler to seek, frame-aligned, ruler scrub                                                                            | `playhead-and-ruler.md` | Skimmer (not in FFP)                                           |
| **Drag/Move (within-track)** | Gapless reorder by midpoint, freeform translate, multi-item drag, snap on freeform                                         | `move.md`               | Cross-track move, new track creation, Alt+drag duplicate       |

### Partially Implemented

These have core logic but missing UI or incomplete interactions — **generate tests for what works, fixme the rest**:

| Feature               | What works                                                                                | What doesn't                                                                            | Phonebook file         |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------- |
| **Snapping**          | Toggle (U key), snap-to-playhead, snap-to-clip-edges, snap indicator line, 10px threshold | Multi-selection snap uses single reference item (FFP-81508), snap UI polish during drag | `snapping.md`          |
| **Freeform behavior** | Tracks exist, items render with gaps, freeform delete/trim/drag work                      | Some interaction edge cases incomplete                                                  | `freeform-behavior.md` |

### Not Implemented

These do not exist in FFP. **Generate only `test.fixme()` stubs** from the phonebook:

| Feature                  | Phonebook file               | Notes                                 |
| ------------------------ | ---------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Copy/Cut/Paste           | `copy-cut-paste.md`          | No clipboard, no Cmd+C/V/X            |
| Duplicate                | `duplicate.md`               | No Alt+drag, no Cmd+D                 |
| Transitions              | `transitions-on-timeline.md` | Schema exists, no UI or transactions  |
| Context menu             | `context-menu.md`            | No right-click menus                  |
| Separate audio           | `separate-audio.md`          | —                                     |
| Cross-track move         | (part of `move.md`)          | No vertical drag between tracks       |
| Connections/choreography | `choreography-rules.md`      | No connected freeform items           |
| Track controls           | (part of `track-types.md`)   | Mute toggle, labels — schema only     |
| Clip properties UI       | —                            | Speed/volume/opacity — no UI controls |

---

## Status Board

Master tracking of phonebook-to-e2e progress. Updated as features are processed.

AC counts come from the implementation map summary table. The actual spec files may have more (the map was written at a point in time; the
specs are the source of truth for generation).

### Ready for generation (implemented in FFP)

Legend: **Active** = tests run in CI. **Active (partial skips)** = file runs, one or more inner tests are `test.skip` or `test.fixme` — see
per-file notes. **Fully skipped** = `test.describe.skip` or equivalent; zero runtime coverage. Phonebook-spec cells are the canonical
phonebook-tagged file; non-phonebook specs covering the same area are listed under "Other active specs" and called out in
`SQUIRREL-TEST-PLAN.md` "Existing Coverage vs. New".

| Feature             | Phonebook file          | Spec file                                            | ACs (map) | Passing | Fixme   | Status                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               |
| ------------------- | ----------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | --------- | ------- | ------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
