# E2E Testing (Playwright against Studio)

**These are Playwright tests. You MUST use Playwright's built-in waiting and assertions — never point-in-time checks.** Playwright locators
auto-wait. Use `expect(locator).toBeVisible()` not `locator.isVisible()`. Use `expect.poll(() => locator.count())` not bare
`locator.count()`. If you find yourself writing a bare check followed by an assertion, you're doing it wrong — Playwright has a waiting
equivalent.

**Before writing or modifying any E2E test, read these files:**

- `docs/studio-e2e-guide.md` — rules, fixtures, page objects, GPU tiers, patterns (includes the "Page Object Pattern (Studio Tenant)"
  doctrine — aggregator + per-surface locators/actions split)
- `e2e/squirrel/README.md` — Squirrel-specific shortcuts, testids, selectors
- `src/applications/squirrel/CLAUDE.md` — the mechanical "Never" list scoped to `e2e/squirrel/**`
- `e2e/studio/README.md` — Studio E2E setup, auth flow, watermelon mock, file structure
- `e2e/studio/CLAUDE.md` — terse cheat-sheet of the Studio page object pattern (hard rules, anti-patterns, "add a new surface" checklist)

## Quick start

```bash
pnpm dev:studio          # Start Studio → https://localhost.adobe.com:3000
pnpm e2e:headless        # Run all E2E tests (fastest)
pnpm e2e:squirrel        # Squirrel tests only
pnpm e2e:studio          # Studio tests only (real IMS auth + mocked generation)
pnpm e2e:swiftshader     # Headless + software GPU (playback works)
pnpm e2e:gpu             # Headed Chrome + real GPU (perf tests)
```

---

## Mental model: Studio is Shadow DOM (Lit)

Every `firefly-*`, `sq-*`, and `sp-*` element has a `shadowRoot`. Standard DOM queries from `page.evaluate()` **cannot find elements inside
shadow roots.** Playwright locators (`getByTestId`, `locator`, `getByRole`) **auto-pierce shadow DOM** by default. **Always prefer
Playwright locators over `page.evaluate` DOM queries.**

### What works vs. what doesn't

| Method                                                                 | Works? | Why                                                             |
| ---------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `page.getByTestId("my-id")`                                            | ✅     | Auto-pierces shadow DOM                                         |
| `page.locator('[data-testid="my-id"]')`                                | ✅     | Same — auto-piercing                                            |
| `page.getByRole("button", { name: "..." })`                            | ✅     | Auto-pierces, accessibility-aware                               |
| `page.evaluate(() => document.querySelector('[data-testid="my-id"]'))` | ❌     | Stops at shadow boundaries                                      |
| XPath locators (`page.locator("//div")`)                               | ❌     | XPath never pierces shadow DOM                                  |
| `element.isVisible()` on `sq-*` host                                   | ⚠️     | Host "visible" while internal content not rendered              |
| `expect(el).toContainText("...")` with slotted content                 | ❌     | Playwright bug #32600 — slots not traversed                     |
| `page.waitForFunction(fn)` for shadow selectors                        | ❌     | Runs in page context — no auto-piercing. **Will hang forever.** |
| `dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent(...))` / `new MouseEvent(...)`        | ❌     | Lit ignores untrusted events; modifier state not propagated     |

---

## Pattern cookbook

### 1. `waitForTimeout` — never use it

```typescript
// Never
await page.waitForTimeout(3000);

// expect.poll for a single-value wait
await expect.poll(() => timelinePage.getPlayheadLeft()).toBeGreaterThan(0);

// Locator auto-wait for DOM state
await expect(timelinePage.gaplessTrackItems.first()).toBeVisible();

// toPass for multi-step async conditions
await expect(async () => {
  const box = await clip.boundingBox();
  expect(box!.width).toBeLessThan(beforeWidth - 5);
}).toPass();
```

No exceptions. Don't pass `{ timeout: ... }` by default — the global 15s timeout is almost always sufficient.

### 2. Synthetic events are ignored by Lit

```typescript
// Wrong — synthetic MouseEvent, ctrlKey ignored
await page.evaluate(el => {
  el.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { ctrlKey: true, bubbles: true }));
}, elementHandle);

// Correct — trusted click via CDP, modifier state propagated
// RULE: always use `ControlOrMeta`. Never `'Control'` or `'Meta'` alone.
await locator.click({ modifiers: ['ControlOrMeta'] });

// Wrong — synthetic KeyboardEvent, Lit handler skips it
await page.evaluate(el => {
  el.dispatchEvent(new KeyboardEvent('keydown', { key: 'S' }));
}, timelineHandle);

// Correct — focus first, then press via CDP
await timelinePage.focusTimeline();
await page.keyboard.press('s');
```

### 3. `waitForFunction` cannot pierce shadow DOM

```typescript
// Wrong — hangs forever for elements inside Web Components
await page.waitForFunction(() => document.querySelector("[data-testid='my-toggle']")?.hasAttribute('checked'));

// Correct
const toggle = page.getByTestId('my-toggle');
await expect(toggle).toHaveAttribute('checked');
```

### 4. Don't walk `shadowRoot` — add `data-testid` instead

```typescript
// Wrong
await page.evaluate(host => {
  const items = host.shadowRoot?.querySelectorAll('.menu-item') ?? [];
  for (const item of items) {
    if (item.textContent?.includes('Mute')) (item as HTMLElement).click();
  }
}, contextMenuHandle);

// Correct
await page.getByTestId('context-menu-item-mute').click();
```

### 5. `networkidle` is unreliable in Studio

```typescript
// Wrong
await page.goto(url, { waitUntil: 'networkidle' });

// Correct
await page.goto(url);
await expect(page.getByTestId('squirrel-timeline')).toBeVisible();
```

### 6. `toPass` vs `expect.poll` — pick the right one

**`toPass`** — assertion callback is `async` (you need to `await` inside):

```typescript
await expect(async () => {
  const box = await clip.boundingBox();
  expect(box!.width).toBeLessThan(beforeWidth - 5);
}).toPass();
```

**`expect.poll`** — factory returns `Promise<T>` but assertion on `T` is sync:

```typescript
await expect.poll(() => timelinePage.getPlayheadLeft()).toBeGreaterThan(0);
```

### 7. `evaluateAll` must be wrapped in `expect.poll`

```typescript
// Wrong — fires once, no retry (RACE CONDITION)
const modes = await page.getByTestId('track-placeholder').evaluateAll(els => els.map(el => el.getAttribute('data-track-mode')));
expect(modes[0]).toBe('freeform');

// Correct
await expect
  .poll(() => page.getByTestId('track-placeholder').evaluateAll(els => els.map(el => el.getAttribute('data-track-mode'))))
  .toSatisfy((modes: string[]) => modes[0] === 'freeform');
```

### 8. Focus before keyboard shortcuts

```typescript
// For pure focus without side effects (no click/seek/selection change):
await timelinePage.focusTimelineKeyboard();
await page.keyboard.press('s');

// Use focusTimeline() only when you want the click side effects too.
```

### 9. Console error detection — assert last

```typescript
test('my test', async ({ page, consoleErrors }) => {
  // ... all test steps ...
  expect(consoleErrors).toEqual([]); // LAST LINE
});
```

### 10. Assertion effectiveness

Before finalizing a test, verify: **"Would reverting the code change cause at least one assertion to fail?"** If no, the test does not
verify the bug.

---

## Studio E2E — real auth + mocked generation

Studio specs live under `e2e/studio/` and run in the `chromium-studio` Playwright project. They differ from Squirrel specs in two ways: real
IMS authentication and a mocked generation backend.

### Playwright project structure

| Project             | Runs                                | Auth                        |
| ------------------- | ----------------------------------- | --------------------------- |
| `studio-setup`      | `e2e/studio/auth.setup.ts` (once)   | Performs real IMS sign-in   |
| `chromium-studio`   | `e2e/studio/tests/**/*.spec.ts`     | Loads `e2e/.auth/user.json` |
| `chromium-headless` | All other specs (squirrel, general) | Dev-mode auth stub          |

`chromium-headless` has `testIgnore: ['studio/**']` — studio specs never double-run there.

### Fixture composition

Studio fixtures are composed with `mergeTests`. Never copy-paste fixture logic — extend the base:

```typescript
import { mergeTests } from '@playwright/test';
import { baseFireflyImageGenerationMockFixture } from '@watermelon/core';
import { test as baseStudioTest } from '../../general/fixtures/base.fixture.js';

const studioOnlyTest = baseStudioTest.extend<MyFixtures>({
  /* ... */
});
export const test = mergeTests(studioOnlyTest, baseFireflyImageGenerationMockFixture());
```

The base fixture gives `studioPage`, `consoleErrors`, `consoleLogs`, and the Vite-overlay handler for free.

### `realAuth=1` URL param

Tests that hit the network (generation, entitlements) need real IMS. Pass `realAuth: true` to `studioPage.open()`:

```typescript
await studioPage.open({ realAuth: true });
```

This swaps the dev-mode auth stub for the real lazy IMS service. The storage state from `studio-setup` supplies the session cookies. **Do
not pass `realAuth: true` in tests that don't need network auth** — it adds overhead and requires `TEST_USERNAME`/`TEST_PASSWORD` to be set.

### Watermelon generation mock

Use `fireflyImageGenerationMock` from `baseFireflyImageGenerationMockFixture`. Register the mock _before_ the user action that triggers the
generation request (not before navigation):

```typescript
// Register before the click that fires the request — not at page load
await fireflyImageGenerationMock.mock({ modelId: 'gemini-flash' });
await studio.generation.locators.generateButton.click();
```

**`modelId` vs `modelVersion`:**

- `modelId` — short 3P discovery ID (e.g. `'gemini-flash'`, `'flux'`, `'imagen4'`). Filters by `body.modelId` in the request; non-matching
  requests pass through.
- `modelVersion` — 1P Firefly model version (e.g. `'image4_standard'`, `'image5'`). Routes to V1/V2 endpoint.
- Omit both for a catch-all that intercepts every generation request.

The mock is **additive** — calling `mock()` twice registers two model configs simultaneously.

### Verifying the mock was called

Use `expect.poll` (not a bare call count check) to handle async timing:

```typescript
